Quanto ao assunto de obter as variáveis. Eu fiz uma função para pegar as variáveis via PUT. Porque depende da página de código, eu uso UTF8 no HTML por ser universal.

Function PegaVar
LOCAL cTemp:="", nRead, nLen, aList, xValue, cArray, cArq
LOCAL cOut, cBuff, cCommand

If "POST" $ Upper( hb_GetEnv( "REQUEST_METHOD" ) )
   nLen := val(hb_getenv("CONTENT_LENGTH"))
   cBuff := space(nLen)
EndIf

Do while .T.

   nRead := FRead( hb_GetStdIn(), @cBuff, hb_BLen( cBuff ) )
   Do case
   case nRead == -1
       OutStd("Erro lendo stdin: " + hb_ntos( ferror()) + hb_eol() )
       exit
   case nRead == 0
       exit
   EndCase

  cOut := hb_BLeft( cBuff, nRead )
  if hb_BLen( cOut ) > 0
     cTemp += cOut
  endif

enddo

/*Se for upload de arquivo*/
If "multipart" $ hb_GetEnv( "CONTENT_TYPE" )
   Return PegaVarMultPart(cTemp)
EndIf

/*
IF "POST" $ Upper( hb_GetEnv( "REQUEST_METHOD" ) )
   nLen := val(hb_getenv("CONTENT_LENGTH"))
   cTemp := Space( nLen )
   IF ( nRead := FRead( hb_GetStdIn(), @cTemp, nLen ) ) != nLen
      //OutStd( "<p>Erro lendo método post " + hb_ntos( nRead ) + " instead of " + hb_ntos( nLen ) )
   ELSE
      //Return OutStd( "<p>Resultado: " + HtmlDecodeUrl(cTemp) + hb_eol() )
   ENDIF
ENDIF
*/

IF empty(cTemp)
   Return ""
ENDIF

aList := hb_RegExSplit( "&", cTemp )

FOR EACH xValue IN aList
    xValue := hb_valtoexp(HtmlDecodeUrl(xValue))
    xValue := StrTran( xValue, "'", "" )
    xValue := StrTran( xValue, "=", ":='" )
    xValue := &xValue + "'"

    If substr(xValue,1,1) == "a" //É um array
       cArray  := substr(xValue,1,at(":",xValue)-1)
       aadd(&cArray, substr( xValue, at("'",xValue)+1, ( rat("'",xValue)-2 - at("'",xValue)+1) ) )
    ELSE
        &xValue
    ENDIF


NEXT


Return ""
